---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import {datetimeSidebar} from '../../../data/datetime-sidebar';
import {Code} from 'astro:components';
import {dep, mavenCentralUrl} from '../../../data/site';
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started with Datetime" sidebar={datetimeSidebar}
            description="Set up Datetime in your Kotlin project">

    <h1>Getting Started</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        Add Datetime to your project and start working with dates, times, and timezones.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Add the dependency</h2>

    <p>In your <code>build.gradle.kts</code>:</p>

    <Code code={`dependencies {
    implementation("${dep.datetime}")
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <p>Find the latest version on <a href={mavenCentralUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maven Central</a>.</p>

    <p>Datetime is a Kotlin Multiplatform library — it works in <code>commonMain</code>, <code>jvmMain</code>,
        <code>jsMain</code>, and <code>nativeMain</code> (linuxX64, linuxArm64, macosX64, macosArm64, mingwX64).</p>

    <h2>2. Create dates and times</h2>

    <p>All types have factory methods and ISO-string parsing:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpLocalDate
import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpLocalTime
import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpLocalDateTime
import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpInstant
import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpTimezone

// From components
val date = MpLocalDate.of(2025, 3, 15)
val time = MpLocalTime.of(14, 30, 0)
val dateTime = MpLocalDateTime.of(2025, 3, 15, 14, 30, 0)

// From ISO strings
val parsed = MpLocalDate.parse("2025-03-15")
val instant = MpInstant.parse("2025-03-15T14:30:00Z")

// Safe parsing
val maybe = MpLocalDate.tryParse("not-a-date")  // null`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>3. Arithmetic</h2>

    <p>Add and subtract days, months, years, and more:</p>

    <Code code={`val date = MpLocalDate.of(2025, 1, 31)

val nextMonth = date.plusMonths(1)    // 2025-02-28 (clamped)
val nextYear = date.plusYears(1)      // 2026-01-31
val lastWeek = date.minusDays(7)     // 2025-01-24

// Anchoring
val startOfMonth = date.atStartOfMonth()     // 2025-01-01
val startOfYear = date.atStartOfYear()       // 2025-01-01
val startOfQuarter = date.atStartOfQuarterOfYear()  // 2025-01-01`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>4. Timezones</h2>

    <p>Convert between absolute and local representations:</p>

    <Code code={`val instant = MpInstant.parse("2025-06-15T12:00:00Z")
val berlin = MpTimezone.of("Europe/Berlin")
val tokyo = MpTimezone.of("Asia/Tokyo")

val inBerlin = instant.atZone(berlin)
println(inBerlin.toLocalDateTime())  // 2025-06-15T14:00 (UTC+2 in summer)

val inTokyo = instant.atZone(tokyo)
println(inTokyo.toLocalDateTime())   // 2025-06-15T21:00 (UTC+9)

// Back to instant
val backToUtc = inBerlin.toInstant()
println(backToUtc == instant)  // true`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>5. Formatting</h2>

    <p>Format dates and times with pattern strings:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.datetime.MpDateTimeFormatter

val formatter = MpDateTimeFormatter("dd MMM yyyy HH:mm")
val zoned = instant.atZone(berlin)

println(zoned.format("dd MMM yyyy"))       // "15 Jun 2025"
println(zoned.format("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm"))  // "2025-06-15 14:00"

// Convenience methods
println(date.formatDdMmmYyyy())  // "15 Jun 2025"`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <Aside>The formatter never throws — malformed patterns degrade gracefully. You'll get output, just maybe not what
        you expected.
    </Aside>

    <h2>6. JVM interop</h2>

    <p>On the JVM, convert seamlessly to and from <code>java.time</code>:</p>

    <Code code={`// Mp -> java.time
val javaInstant: java.time.Instant = mpInstant.jvm
val javaDate: java.time.LocalDate = mpDate.jvm
val javaZoned: java.time.ZonedDateTime = mpZoned.jvm

// java.time -> Mp
val mpInstant: MpInstant = javaInstant.mp
val mpDate: MpLocalDate = javaDate.mp
val mpZoned: MpZonedDateTime = javaZoned.mp`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <div class="not-prose mt-8 flex gap-4">
        <a href="/ultra/datetime/types"
           class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-brand-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-500 transition-colors">
            Core types &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>

</DocsLayout>
